### Phase 6b: Slide Deck Generation (Primary Output)

**Objective:** Generate a branded Workday slide deck using the Slide Deck MCP (`user-slide-deck-mcp`).

**Canonical baseline (repo):** Before drafting `slides_spec.json` or `slides_spec_vN.json`, read **`docs/decks/gcc-pmf-roadmap-baseline-slides-spec.md`** for mandatory **section order**, **36–50 slide** guardrails, and layout expectations. For a fast skeleton, copy the **structure** (section dividers, slide sequence, `layout_name` pattern) from the latest **`slides_spec_v*.json`** in the project root, then replace all content from the current PMF report—do **not** ship fewer than **36 slides** or omit standard sections unless the PM explicitly requests a **focus deck**.

**MCP Workflow:**
1. Call `parse_template` for template_path
2. Write slide spec JSON to `slides_spec.json` (or `slides_spec_vN.json`) at project root
3. Call `create_presentation` or run `generate_presentation.py`
4. Output to `~/Downloads/[Country]_Recruiting_PMF_Roadmap_vN.pptx` — version auto-increments on each generation (v1, v2, v3…)

**Slide spec schema (mandatory — matches `user-slide-deck-mcp` `create_presentation`):**
- Use **`layout_name`** on every slide (e.g. `"TITLE"`, `"Title Only"`, `"Title Only_Alt"`, `"Section Title"`, `"1/2 Headline_Alt"`, `"Bumper Slide"`). Do **not** use a top-level `"layout"` key; the engine ignores it and may render every slide as a title slide.
- **`placeholders`** must map indices to objects: `"0": {"text": "Title"}`. Never use `"0": "plain string"`.
- **Section Title** has no title placeholder; use two **`text_boxes`**: heading at `(3.3, 1.5)` 24pt bold `ink`, subtitle at `(3.3, 3.8)` 11pt `laptop` (see working `slides_spec.json` in repo).

**Deck Structure (target length 36-50 slides, McKinsey-style tone):**

**MANDATORY: Every new versioned deck (v41, v42, v45, etc.) MUST include ALL sections below unless user explicitly requests a "focus deck."**

1. **Title + Executive Summary** (2 slides)
   - Title: [Region] Recruiting Product-Market Fit Research
   - Executive Summary: Key themes, PESTEL headlines, E2E handoff summary

2. **SECTION: Research Challenge** (3 slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Research Challenge | Objectives and methodology"
   - Research Question & Objectives
   - 5-Phase Framework (Braun & Clarke phases 0-6)

3. **SECTION: Context Review** (2+ slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Context Review | Strategic context and market momentum"
   - Strategic Context (market size, growth, digital transformation)

4. **SECTION: PESTEL Analysis** (7 slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "PESTEL Analysis | Political, Economic, Social, Technological, Environmental, Legal"
   - Political (full slide with nationalization mandates, penalties)
   - Economic (full slide with market data, CAGR, investment trends)
   - Social (full slide with communication channel stats, smartphone penetration, cultural factors)
   - Technological (full slide with AI, government portals, integrations)
   - Environmental (full slide, DATA GAP if no recruiting signal)
   - Legal (full slide with PDPL, interview regulations, compliance requirements)

5. **SECTION: Competitive Landscape** (2 slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Competitive Landscape | Regional specialists vs global platforms"
   - Competitive Landscape (global enterprise vs regional specialists breakdown)

6. **SECTION: Win/Loss Overview** (2 slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Win/Loss Overview | [Region]-explicit gaps"
   - GCC-Relevant Win/Loss Gaps (table with Gap ID, Pain Point, Severity)

7. **SECTION: Primary Research** (5+ slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Primary Research | Interview participants"
   - Interview Participants (P1, P2, P3 with roles and companies)
   - P1 - [Company]: Key Themes (detailed bullets with quotes)
   - P2 - [Company]: Key Themes (detailed bullets with quotes)
   - P3 - [Company]: Key Themes (detailed bullets with quotes)

8. **SECTION: Thematic Analysis** (4+ slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Thematic Analysis | Validated themes and triangulation"
   - Validated Themes 1-3 (or 1-4 if >6 themes)
   - Validated Themes 4-6 (or 5-7 if >7 themes)
   - Cross-Source Validation Matrix (triangulation table: Theme | P1 | P2 | P3 | CSV | PMF Impact)

9. **SECTION: Roadmap Recommendations** (8+ slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Roadmap Recommendations | Priority 1 and Priority 2"
   - Recommendation 1: [Title] (5-part: Problem, Evidence, Recommendation, Why now, Success Metrics)
   - Recommendation 2: [Title]
   - Recommendation 3: [Title]
   - Recommendation 4: [Title]
   - Recommendation 5: [Title]
   - Recommendation 6: [Title] (if applicable)
   - E2E Handoff: N Recommendations for PM Selection (numbered table slide)

10. **Bumper Slide**

**Canonical baseline enforcement:** `slides_spec.json` MUST contain the full 36-50 slide structure above as the working baseline. When generating versioned decks (v41+), the agent MUST:
1. Start from `slides_spec.json` structure
2. Populate with fresh analysis content from the report
3. Add any version-specific deep-dive slides AFTER the standard sections
4. Never skip or compress standard sections unless user says "focus deck only"

**Compressed decks are forbidden by default.** If a versioned deck has <36 slides or is missing PESTEL/Win/Loss/Interview sections, it violates the standard.

**Participant Anonymization:**
- Customer interview participants: List as "P1 - Job Title, Company" (e.g., "P1 - Senior Recruiter, Accenture")
- Apply consistently on Interview Participants slide, customer detail slides, triangulation matrices, and all quotes

**Recommendation Slide Structure (5-part):** Problem | Evidence | Recommendation | Why now | Success Metrics

**Before finalizing Roadmap Recommendations (Section 06)**: Invoke **060-legal-advisor** to review recommendations for legal/compliance implications (GDPR, AI Act, local regulations). Legal Advisor validates "Why now" and "Recommendation" for compliance. Address any flags before generating deck.

**Speaker Notes (MANDATORY for content slides):**
- Add `speaker_notes` to every content slide except TITLE, Section Title, Bumper Slide
- Format: Bullet-pointed presenter guidance, then "References:" with live, working URLs
- Include references for all sources used (Mondaq, Astute Analytica, Braun & Clarke, etc.)

**Product Implication (PESTEL slides):**
- Each PESTEL slide ends with "Product implication:" — bold, same font size as bullets, yellow highlight. The generate_presentation pipeline applies this automatically.

**Chart requirements:**

- **One label per bar:** Use exactly one series for simple bar charts (e.g. Win/Loss Top 10) so each category gets one bar and one Y-axis label. For stacked bars (e.g. Ideation Hub), use `bar_stacked` — each category gets one stacked bar.
- **Font sizes:** Always include `category_axis_font_size_pt: 9`, `value_axis_font_size_pt: 9`, `title_font_size_pt: 10` to keep chart text readable.

**Table requirements:**
- **Font size:** Use 7-9pt for table content (7pt for dense content like SWOT analysis)
- **Headers:** Navy background (`ink`) with white text (`paper`)
- **Header height:** Use `header_height_inches: 0.25` for compact headers
- **SWOT Analysis:** Use two separate tables (one for Strengths/Weaknesses at `top_inches: 1.0`, one for Opportunities/Threats at `top_inches: 3.15`) to ensure all headers have proper formatting
- **Height:** Use `height_inches: 2.1` per table for SWOT analysis to fit content properly
- **Example SWOT configuration:**
```json
"tables": [
  {
    "rows": [["Strengths", "Weaknesses"], ["...", "..."]],
    "top_inches": 1.0,
    "height_inches": 2.1,
    "font_size_pt": 7,
    "header_row": true,
    "header_bg_color": "ink",
    "header_font_color": "paper",
    "header_height_inches": 0.25
  },
  {
    "rows": [["Opportunities", "Threats"], ["...", "..."]],
    "top_inches": 3.15,
    "height_inches": 2.1,
    "font_size_pt": 7,
    "header_row": true,
    "header_bg_color": "ink",
    "header_font_color": "paper",
    "header_height_inches": 0.25
  }
]
```

**Content positioning:**
- Body text: `top_inches: 1.2` (not 1.6) to avoid excess vertical gap between title and content
- Tables: Start at `top_inches: 0.95` or `1.0` for maximum space utilization

